issue.title: gitian-linux: Build binaries for 64-bit POWER
issue.body:
A set of both big and little endian binaries, should be compatible with PowerPC 970 (Apple G5) and newer.

~~Also splits libpng out of Qt (since Qt's bundled copy is broken on POWER) and disables JPEG (since we don't use it).~~

Tested only the little endian variant, on Gentoo.

~~(Based on #14065)~~

issue.title: Minor style enhancement in documentation
issue.body:
It is considered a best practice to avoid noun+verb contractions in technical documentation as it makes it easier to read, especially for non native English speakers.
As a reference: https://developers.google.com/style/contractions

events.body: I'm going ahead and merging this, @luke-jr please rebase your stuff on top.
